  "prompt": "If I connect USB OTG pendrive to my power bank and connect the other point with data cable to my mobile, will pendrive be working on my mobile?",
  "response": "Using a USB OTG (On-The-Go) cable or adapter is the correct method for connecting a pendrive directly to a mobile device to access the files stored on the pendrive. However, your described setup\u2014connecting a USB OTG pendrive directly to a power bank and then connecting the power bank to your mobile device with a data cable\u2014will not work for transferring data or accessing the files on the pendrive.\n\nHere\u2019s why:\n\n1. **OTG Functionality**: The OTG feature allows a mobile device to act as a host for peripherals like USB drives. For the device to access the pendrive, the pendrive must be directly connected to the mobile device through an OTG adapter.\n\n2. **Power Bank Role**: Power banks are primarily designed to provide power to devices, not to facilitate data transfer. They do not have the capability to act as a data conduit between a pendrive and a mobile device.\n\nSo, to use the pendrive with your mobile device, you should connect the pendrive directly to your mobile using a USB OTG adapter. Make sure your mobile device supports OTG functionality and that the pendrive is formatted in a file system compatible with your device (like FAT32).",
